article.description: Hooker, North Dakota hold off Montana St, 67-60
article.headline: Hooker, North Dakota hold off Montana St, 67-60
article.linkText: Hooker, North Dakota hold off Montana St, 67-60
article.story: BOZEMAN, Mont. -- Quinton Hooker scored 16 points to lead North Dakota past Montana State 67-60 in the Big Sky opener for both teams on Thursday. Carson Shanks added 12 points and Lenny Antwi scored 10 for North Dakota(5-7). Eric Norman made a layup with 4 minutes left, pulling Montana State within three, 54-51, but Shanks made two free throws and, after a Montana State turnover, Dustin Hobaugh hit a 3-pointer to push the North Dakota lead to eight with 2:16 remaining. A four-point play by Danny Robison pulled Montana State (3-10) to 61-56 with 1:39 to go. After getting a stop on the other end, the Bobcats called timeout before turning it over on a five-second violation. A layup by Shanks with 43 seconds left gave North Dakota a 63-56 lead and Estan Tyler and Hooker each hit two free throws down the stretch to seal it. Michael Dison led Montana State with 22 points.
